				\begin{document}$${\text{Inhibition rate}}\left( \% \right) = \left( {1 - \frac{T}{C}} \right) \times 100\%$$\end{document}Inhibition rate%=1-TC×100%where T is the average number of local lesions of treatment, C is the average number of local lesions of negative control. All experiments were conducted in triplicate. TMV was stored in systemic host Nicotiana tabacum K326 and purified as described by Gooding and Hebert (1967).

